<p>Pricing is identical. So the decision comes down to actual usefulness, not cost.</p>

<h2>Free tier comparison, what you actually get without paying</h2>

<h3>ChatGPT free tier</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Access to GPT-4o (limited) and GPT-4o mini (unlimited)</li>
  <li>Image generation (limited per day)</li>
  <li>Voice mode</li>
  <li>Web browsing</li>
  <li>Custom GPTs (use, not create)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Claude free tier</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Access to Claude Sonnet, daily message limit</li>
  <li>File uploads (PDFs, images, docs)</li>
  <li>Web search</li>
  <li>Projects (basic)</li>
  <li>Artifacts (live previews of code, docs, designs)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Verdict on free tiers:</strong> ChatGPT's free tier feels broader (image gen + voice). Claude's feels deeper (better core model, artifacts are genuinely useful). For most Indian writing/coding/research work, Claude's free tier produces better output.</p>

<h2>Performance on Indian use cases</h2>

<h3>Hinglish and Indian English</h3>
<p>I tested both on prompts like "draft a polite WhatsApp message to my landlord in Bengaluru about the leaking ceiling, slightly Hinglish but professional." Claude produces more natural Indian-flavored English. ChatGPT's output reads more like American business English with occasional Hindi words pasted in.</p>

<h3>Hindi content generation</h3>
<p>Both handle Hindi well now. ChatGPT is slightly faster on Hindi. Claude is slightly better at retaining tone across long Hindi pieces.</p>

<h3>Tax, GST, Indian compliance queries</h3>
<p>Claude tends to be more cautious and accurate on Indian regulatory questions, but you should never rely on either for actual tax filing. Both are useful for understanding concepts; neither replaces a CA.</p>

<h3>Long documents (legal, contracts, research papers)</h3>
<p><strong>Claude wins clearly.</strong> Its context window and reasoning on long documents is currently unmatched. If you're an Indian lawyer, CA, or researcher, this alone justifies Claude.</p>

<h3>Image generation and creative visual work</h3>
<p><strong>ChatGPT wins clearly.</strong> Built-in DALL-E and image editing make it the better pick for marketers and creators who want everything in one place.</p>

