<h2>Privacy and data, does it matter for Indian users?</h2>

<p>Anthropic (Claude) has stricter default data policies, they don't train on consumer chat data by default. OpenAI does train on free-tier chats unless you opt out. For Indian CAs, lawyers, and small business owners working with sensitive client data, this is a meaningful difference.</p>

<h2>Decision framework</h2>

<p><strong>Pick Claude if you:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Write a lot (blogs, emails, reports, content)</li>
  <li>Work with long documents (legal drafts, research, contracts)</li>
  <li>Code (Claude's coding output is currently top-tier)</li>
  <li>Want better default privacy</li>
  <li>Mostly need text reasoning, not images</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Pick ChatGPT if you:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Need image generation and voice in one tool</li>
  <li>Use custom GPTs for specific workflows</li>
  <li>Want broader plugin and integration ecosystem</li>
  <li>Do social media work that needs visuals</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Pick both if you can afford ₹4,000/month.</strong> Many Indian power users run both subscriptions. They're complementary, not redundant.</p>

<h2>Indian-specific FAQs</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Can I claim GST input credit on ChatGPT or Claude subscription?</h3>
  <p>If you're a registered GST business and use the tool for business purposes, yes, you can claim the 18% GST as input credit. You'll need a tax invoice with your GSTIN. Both tools can issue tax invoices on request through their billing support.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Are these tools blocked or restricted in India?</h3>
  <p>No. Both ChatGPT and Claude are fully accessible in India without VPN as of 2026.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Which is better for Indian competitive exam prep?</h3>
  <p>For UPSC, JEE, NEET, Claude tends to give more nuanced answers on humanities and reasoning. ChatGPT is faster on math and quick fact recall. Most students benefit from using both.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>I'm a freelancer in India. Which one for client work?</h3>
  <p>Claude. Better long-form output, better at maintaining tone, and the privacy default matters when handling client data. Read our full <a href="/for/freelancers/">guide for Indian freelancers</a>.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Will ChatGPT or Claude understand Kannada, Tamil, Telugu, or Marathi?</h3>
  <p>Both handle major Indian languages reasonably. Claude is slightly better at Tamil and Bengali. ChatGPT handles Marathi and Gujarati slightly better. For Hindi, both are now production-quality.</p>
</div>

<h2>Final recommendation</h2>

<p>If I had to pick one for an Indian user in 2026, it would be Claude. Better text quality, better long documents, better privacy default, identical price.</p>

<p>If your work is image-heavy or you need voice + plugins, get ChatGPT.</p>

<p>If you can afford both, run both, they each have moments where they outperform.</p>

